abstract: >-
  RowVoi provides a set of tools for interactive
  disambiguation of rows in a dataset using value of
  information policies. Given a small set of candidate rows,
  it helps determine which columns (features) must be
  observed to uniquely distinguish these rows, using both
  deterministic set cover algorithms and probabilistic
  Îµ-relaxed approaches. The package implements multiple
  algorithms including exact and greedy minimal key finding,
  mutual information-based feature selection, and adaptive
  policies that respond to observations.
